          <h1 class="sub-heading font-weight-bold">The Solution</h1>
          <p class="case-study-text">
            What gets measured gets improved!
            We all have heard it many times over but curiously enough, there isn’t a way to measure the amount of time we all end up wasting on a Facebook or Instagram or Twitter.
            EyzUp’s approach is to measure the time spent on apps, set goals for time spent on high usage apps and then use this as a guiding structure to reduce the addiction to apps and spend more time in real social interactions with friends and family.
            The feature set was designed keeping in mind BJ Fogg’s behaviour model of B=MAT [B=Behaviour, M=Motivation, A=Ability, T=Trigger]. The app is designed to provide its users’ a motivation, ability and trigger to change their behaviour of spending large amounts of time on their smart devices and spend more time in the real world.
            We built EyzUp considering two personas.
            <ol>
              <li>James - 30 year old single male professional who spends a lot of time on the virtual social world.</li>
              <li>Mary and Mike - Mary a working mother, is looking for a tool she can use to monitor the usage behaviour of Mike, her son to ensure that Mike doesn’t get addicted to smart devices very early on.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </div>
