<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
        <div class="hidden-xs">
          <h1 class="sub-heading font-weight-bold">Product/Key Features</h1>
          <p class="case-study-text">
            <p>The app is currently being used by about 150 early adopters in Singapore, Thailand, Malaysia and the United Kingdom.</p>
            <h3>Features for James:</h3>
            <ol>
              <li>Social Login - Google and Facebook</li>
              <li>Usage Reports - Total phone usage and detailed app usage (Today and Yesterday)</li>
              <li>Daily Usage Limits for Apps
                <ol>
                  <li>Soft limits - 3 levels of warning when the user cross the limit using the color codes to help the user resist the urge to constantly checking his phone.</li>
                  <li>Hard Limit - Temporarily blocks the app after exhausting the usage limit. The app will be enabled after 24 hours.</li>
                  <li>Maximum usage limit allowed for any app is 90 mins (as studies have shown that constant usage of an app for more than 90mins is a sign of addiction)</li>
                </ol>
              </li>
              <li>EyzUp Time - Similar to do-not-disturb profile which help the user schedule phone - away time.
                <ol>
                  <li>With black listing of apps, limiting users to 5 whitelisted apps</li>
                  <li>Blocking notifications from the blacklisted apps in EyzUp time</li>
                  <li>Repeat features</li>
                </ol>
              </li>
              <li>Notification on yesterday’s most used app.</li>
              <li>Cloud backup</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Features for Mary(mother) and Mike(son)</h3>
            <ol>
              <li>Child device registration with QR code.
                <ol>
                  <li>3 step registration process</li>
                </ol>
              </li>
              <li>Support multiple child devices</li>
              <li>Parent and child de-addiction - Switching between child and parent profiles.</li>
              <li>Child device listing in the parent app.</li>
              <li>EyzUp time for the kids like sleep time, dinner time, study time</li>
              <li>Reporting the all the apps installed on the child device.</li>
              <li>Usage reports from the child device delivered in the parent app</li>
              <li>Daily usage limit for parent and child devices.</li>
              <li>Child device only shows the reports, all the other configuration are hidden in the child device. This is to give more control to the parent.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
